\u003dhttps://x.com/AndFidian\u0026ctx\u003div\u0026hl\u003den-NG"],"2008":[null,"Fidian Chops (@AndFidian) / Posts / X"]}],"jQvhaeKtOYDpi-gPyYGpmAc139":[1,[0,"Z3oNbffmO3OngM",["https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q\u003dtbn:ANd9GcRBZJ3sfo31vP9CuiviUvL0o7eI2HcVouZqfA\u0026s",194,259],["https://www.bigfattummy.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Fried-Mutton-Chops-005-1200x900.jpg",900,1200],null,1,"rgb(152,117,75)",null,0,{"2000":[null,"www.bigfattummy.com","123KB"],"2001":[null,null,null,null,null,9,3],"2003":[null,"3jQbSYCnCyZP_M","https://www.bigfattummy.com/2017/04/fried-mutton-chops/","Fried Mutton Chops",null,0,null,null,null,0,null,null,"Big Fat Tummy",null,null,null,null,"www.bigfattummy.com",null,null,null,null,null,null,0,[null,2],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,"https://www.google.com/search/about-this-image?img\u003dH4sIAAAAAAAA_-MS4bj38s2Jlg8vW9UEnn_Z-uLbvZ9ziwFa2bVpFgAAAA%3D%3D\u0026q\u003dhttps://www.bigfattummy.com/2017/04/fried-mutton-chops/\u0026ctx\u003div\u0026hl\u003den-NG"],"2006":[[null,null,"Fried Mutton Chops",["The Fried Mutton Chops are a perfect starter. They are mildly spiced and  taste good hot or cold. You can serve these as a side dish, accompanied  with a pulao., Serves: 4 Persons, Prep. Time: 15 Mins. + 1 to 2 Hrs.  (marination), Cooking Time: 25 to 30 Mins., Ingredients:, Mutton Chops –  500 gms.Lime – 1 bigEggs – 2For the Marinade:, Ginger – 1 inch, Garlic – 12  to 15 small, Green Chillies – 2 to 3, Cumin Seeds – ½ tsp., Black Pepper  Corns – 1 tsp., Turmeric – ½ tsp., Garam Masala / Meat Masala Powder - ½  tsp., Oil – 2 tbsp.Salt – 1 tsp., Step 1:","Wash the chops and drain well. Apply salt and lime juice and leave aside  for 10 minutes., Step 2:","Grind all the ingredients for the marinade to a fine paste using 2 tbsp.  water., Step 3:","Apply the paste to the chops and leave to marinate for 1 to 2 hours in the  refrigerator., Step 4:","After the chops have marinated, pressure cook them with 3 tbsp. water on  high heat till the 1st whistle. Then lower the heat and cook for 10 to 12  minutes. Switch off the heat and let the pressure reduce naturally (the  chops should be cooked tender but not falling off the bone)., Step 5:"],"These Fried Mutton Chops are mildly spiced and taste good hot or cold. You  can serve these as a side ...",null,"The Fried Mutton Chops are a perfect starter. They are mildly spiced and  taste good hot or cold. You can serve these as a side dish, accompanied  with a pulao., Serves: 4 Persons, Prep. Time: 15 Mins. + 1 to 2 Hrs.  (marination), Cooking Time: 25 to 30 Mins., Ingredients:, Mutton Chops –  500 gms.Lime – 1 bigEggs – 2For the Marinade:, Ginger – 1 inch, Garlic – 12  to 15 small, Green Chillies – 2 to 3, Cumin Seeds – ½ tsp., Black Pepper  Corns – 1 tsp., Turmeric – ½ tsp., Garam Masala / Meat Masala Powder - ½  tsp., Oil – 2 tbsp.Salt – 1 tsp., Step 1: Wash the chops and drain well.  Apply salt and lime juice and leave aside for 10 minutes., Step 2: Grind  all the ingredients for the marinade to a fine paste using 2 tbsp. water.,  Step 3: Apply the paste to the chops and leave to marinate for 1 to 2 hours  in the refrigerator., Step 4: After the chops have marinated, pressure cook  them with 3 tbsp. water on high heat till the 1st whistle. Then lower the  heat and cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Switch off the heat and let the  pressure reduce naturally (the chops should be cooked tender but not  falling off the bone)., Step 5: Open the lid of the pressure cooker and  place on heat. Cook uncovered on medium heat to dry out any liquids. The  thick masala should coat the chops well. Switch off the heat., Step 6: Beat  the eggs with a pinch of salt., Step 7: Heat 2 tbsp. oil in a non-stick  pan. Dip the chops in the beaten eggs to coat a chop well and shallow fry  each coated chop on medium heat for 2 minutes on each side till golden  brown."]],"2008":[null,"Fried Mutton Chops Recipe - BFT .. for ..."]}],null,null,null,null,null,"Z3oNbffmO3OngM",null,null,null,null,null,null,[null,0]],"jQvhaeKtOYDpi-gPyYGpmAc143":[0,"Z3oNbffmO3OngM",["https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q\u003dtbn:ANd9GcRBZJ3sfo31vP9CuiviUvL0o7eI2HcVouZqfA\u0026s",194,259],["https://www.bigfattummy.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/Fried-Mutton-Chops-005-1200x900.jpg",900,1200],null,1,"rgb(152,117,75)",null,0,{"2000":[null,"www.bigfattummy.com","123KB"],"2001":[null,null,null,null,null,9,3],"2003":[null,"3jQbSYCnCyZP_M","https://www.bigfattummy.com/2017/04/fried-mutton-chops/","Fried Mutton Chops",null,0,null,null,null,0,null,null,"Big Fat Tummy",null,null,null,null,"www.bigfattummy.com",null,null,null,null,null,null,0,[null,2],null,null,null,null,null,null,null,"https://www.google.com/search/about-this-image?img\u003dH4sIAAAAAAAA_-MS4bj38s2Jlg8vW9UEnn_Z-uLbvZ9ziwFa2bVpFgAAAA%3D%3D\u0026q\u003dhttps://www.bigfattummy.com/2017/04/fried-mutton-chops/\u0026ctx\u003div\u0026hl\u003den-NG"],"2006":[[null,null,"Fried Mutton Chops",["The Fried Mutton Chops are a perfect starter. They are mildly spiced and  taste good hot or cold. You can serve these as a side dish, accompanied  with a pulao., Serves: 4 Persons, Prep. Time: 15 Mins. + 1 to 2 Hrs.  (marination), Cooking Time: 25 to 30 Mins., Ingredients:, Mutton Chops –  500 gms.Lime – 1 bigEggs – 2For the Marinade:, Ginger – 1 inch, Garlic – 12  to 15 small, Green Chillies – 2 to 3, Cumin Seeds – ½ tsp., Black Pepper  Corns – 1 tsp., Turmeric – ½ tsp., Garam Masala / Meat Masala Powder - ½  tsp., Oil – 2 tbsp.Salt – 1 tsp., Step 1:","Wash the chops and drain well. Apply salt and lime juice and leave aside  for 10 minutes., Step 2:","Grind all the ingredients for the marinade to a fine paste using 2 tbsp.  water., Step 3:","Apply the paste to the chops and leave to marinate for 1 to 2 hours in the  refrigerator., Step 4:","After the chops have marinated, pressure cook them with 3 tbsp. water on  high heat till the 1st whistle. Then lower the heat and cook for 10 to 12  minutes. Switch off the heat and let the pressure reduce naturally (the  chops should be cooked tender but not falling off the bone)., Step 5:"],"These Fried Mutton Chops are mildly spiced and taste good hot or cold. You  can serve these as a side ...",null,"The Fried Mutton Chops are a perfect starter. They are mildly spiced and  taste good hot or cold. You can serve these as a side dish, accompanied  with a pulao., Serves: 4 Persons, Prep. Time: 15 Mins. + 1 to 2 Hrs.  (marination), Cooking Time: 25 to 30 Mins., Ingredients:, Mutton Chops –  500 gms.Lime – 1 bigEggs – 2For the Marinade:, Ginger – 1 inch, Garlic – 12  to 15 small, Green Chillies – 2 to 3, Cumin Seeds – ½ tsp., Black Pepper  Corns – 1 tsp., Turmeric – ½ tsp., Garam Masala / Meat Masala Powder - ½  tsp., Oil – 2 tbsp.Salt – 1 tsp., Step 1: Wash the chops and drain well.  Apply salt and lime juice and leave aside for 10 minutes., Step 2: Grind  all the ingredients for the marinade to a fine paste using 2 tbsp. water.,  Step 3: Apply the paste to the chops and leave to marinate for 1 to 2 hours  in the refrigerator., Step 4: After the chops have marinated, pressure cook  them with 3 tbsp. water on high heat till the 1st whistle. Then lower the  heat and cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Switch off the heat and let the  pressure reduce naturally (the chops should be cooked tender but not  falling off the bone)., Step 5: Open the lid of the pressure cooker and  place on heat. Cook uncovered on medium heat to dry out any liquids. The  thick masala should coat the chops well. Switch off the heat., Step 6: Beat  the eggs with a pinch of salt., Step 7: Heat 2 tbsp. oil in a non-stick  pan. Dip the chops in the beaten eggs to coat a chop well and shallow fry  each coated chop on medium heat for 2 minutes on each side till golden  brown."]],"2008":[null,"Fried Mutton Chops Recipe - BFT .. for ..."]}],"jQvhaeKtOYDpi-gPyYGpmAc147":[1,[0,"euAHVBS4MshaxM",["https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q\u003dtbn:ANd9GcTK5yWn941_V_IMGQbpXA6uoXo2GJ4D0u1uLg\u0026s",183